<     printf("Hello, World!\n");
<     return 0;
< }
< ```
> scrivi un programma che stampa ciao mondo
< Verified by execution: it prints "ciao mondo" and exits 0 (print_message schema, run via the code_run oracle).
< 
< ```c
< #include <stdio.h>
< 
< int main(void) {
<     printf("ciao mondo\n");
<     return 0;
< }
< ```
> costruisci una calcolatrice in python
< I understood the request — produce "calcolatrice" in python — but I don't have a verified schema for that artifact yet; I only synthesize what an oracle can check (a sort from a learned shape, arithmetic composition, a count-to-threshold game).

